      • setBinaryHierarchyLength

        public void setBinaryHierarchyLength(Integer length)
        Set the character length of intermediate path components for internal binary resource identifiers.

        Note: for POSIX filesystems there are performance consideration for placing many files in a single directory. Using such intermediate directories can significantly improve performance. Setting this to "2" results in a maximum of 256 subdirectories in each intermediate segment. Values between 1 and 3 are suitable for most cases.

        Parameters:
        length - the character length of each hierarchy segment

      • getBinaryHierarchyLength

        public Integer getBinaryHierarchyLength()
        Get the character length of intermediate path components for internal binary resource identifiers.

        Note: for POSIX filesystems there are performance consideration for placing many files in a single directory. Using such intermediate directories can significantly improve performance. Setting this to "2" results in a maximum of 256 subdirectories in each intermediate segment. Values between 1 and 3 are suitable for most cases.

        Returns:
        the character length of each hierarchy segment

      • setBinaryHierarchyLevels

        public void setBinaryHierarchyLevels(Integer levels)
        Set the number of levels of hierarchy for internal binary resource identifiers.

        Note: for POSIX filesystems there are performance consideration for placing many files in a single directory. Using such intermediate directories can significantly improve performance. Values between 2 and 4 are generally suitable for most uses.

        Parameters:
        levels - the number of levels of hierarchy.
